body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Premium Motors. My name is Willie Anderson. May I have your name please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hi Willie, my name is Sarah Diaz.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Sarah. Can you please spell out your phone number digit by digit?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's six four five, three five two, zero one two three.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Sarah. And may I have your email address, letter by letter?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for providing the information. Is there anything specific you are interested in discussing today, Sarah?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm actually looking for information on pricing for the latest models.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I'm happy to assist with that. Let's explore the pricing options together. Thank you for your time, Sarah. Have a wonderful day!

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Thank you, Willie. I appreciate your help. Goodbye!
